      • getCipher

        public Cipher getCipher(String salt,
                        int mode,
                        BigInteger secret)
                 throws UnsupportedEncodingException,
                        NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                        InvalidKeySpecException,
                        NoSuchPaddingException,
                        InvalidKeyException,
                        InvalidAlgorithmParameterException
        Provide a Cipher for de/encryption, use the provided secret, if not null. If secret is null, the SecretBean will provide the secret.
        Parameters:
        salt - the salt for the Cipher, see PBEKeySpec
        mode - en/decryption mode, see Cipher.init(int, java.security.Key)
        secret - the secret
        Returns:
        Throws:
